cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the problem of embedding information flows in cover traffic to avoid detection, which is a common problem in secure networking (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of the maximum flow rate (cs.IT) and the modeling of cover traffic as a renewal process (cs.NI). The paper uses analytical expressions to explore the properties of the embedding capacity (cs.SI) and tests the solution on real network traces (cs.DS).
